. 
. foreach i in 1 2 3 4{
  5. 
. sum `w' [aw=w1anfinwgt0] if homebound_cat1 == `i', detail
  6. mat test1[`r',`c'] = r(sum)
  7. mat test1[`r',`c'+1] = r(mean)*100
  8. svy: tab `w' homebound_cat1 if homebound_cat1 == `i' | homebound_cat1 == 1

. local c = 1

. foreach w in eat bath toil dres insd bed  {
  2. 
. foreach i in 1 2 3 4{
  3. 
. sum op_adl_`w' if homebound_cat1 == `i' [aw=w1anfinwgt0], detail
  4. mat test1[`r',`c']=r(sum)
  5. mat test1[`r',`c'+1] = r(mean)*100
  6. svy: tab op_adl_`w' homebound_cat1 if homebound_cat1 == `i' | homebound_cat1 == 1
  7. mat test1[`r',`c'+2] = e(p_Pear)
  8. local c = `c' + 3
  9. }
 10. 
. local r = `r' + 1
 11. local c = 1
 12. 
. }

. local r = 30

. local c = 1

. 
. foreach w in laun shop meal bank  meds {
  2. 
. foreach i in 1 2 3 4{
  3. 
. sum op_iadl_`w' if homebound_cat1 == `i' [aw=w1anfinwgt0], detail
  4. mat test1[`r',`c']=r(sum)
  5. mat test1[`r',`c'+1] = r(mean)*100
  6. svy: tab op_iadl_`w' homebound_cat1 if homebound_cat1 == `i' | homebound_cat1 == 1
  7. mat test1[`r',`c'+2] = e(p_Pear)
  8. local c = `c' + 3
  9. 
. }
 10. 
. local r = `r' + 1
 11. local c = 1
 12. 
. }

. 
. local r = 19

. local c = 1

. foreach w in eat bath toil dres insd bed  {
  2. foreach i in 1 2 3 4{
  3. 
. sum op_adl_`w' if homebound_cat1 == `i' [aw=w1anfinwgt0], detail
  4. mat test1[`r',`c']=r(sum)
  5. mat test1[`r',`c'+1] = r(mean)*100
  6. svy: tab op_adl_`w' homebound_cat1 if homebound_cat1 == 1 | homebound_cat1 == `i'
  7. mat test1[`r',`c'+2] = e(p_Pear)
  8. local c = `c' + 3
  9. }
 10. 
. local r = `r' + 1
 11. local c = 1
 12. 
. }

. local c = 1

  2. foreach i in 1 2 3 4{
  3.

  4. mat test1[`r',`c']=r(sum)
  5. mat test1[`r',`c'+1] = r(mean)*100
  6. svy: tab op_iadl_`w' homebound_cat1 if homebound_cat1 == 1 | homebound_cat1 == `i'
  7. mat test1[`r',`c'+2] = e(p_Pear)
  8. local c = `c' + 3
  9. }

. local r = `r' + 1

. 
. local r = 30

. local c = 1

. 
. foreach w in laun shop meal bank  meds {
  2. 
. foreach i in 1 2 3 4{
  3. 
. sum op_iadl_`w' if homebound_cat1 == `i' [aw=w1anfinwgt0], detail
  4. mat test1[`r',`c']=r(sum)
  5. mat test1[`r',`c'+1] = r(mean)*100
  6. svy: tab op_iadl_`w' homebound_cat1 if homebound_cat1 == `i' | homebound_cat1 == 1
  7. mat test1[`r',`c'+2] = e(p_Pear)
  8. local c = `c' + 3
  9. 
. }
 10. 
. local r = `r' + 1
 11. local c = 1
 12. 
. }

. local r = 19

. local c = 1

. foreach w in eat bath toil dres insd bed  {
  2. foreach i in 1 2 3 4{
  3. 
. sum op_adl_`w' if homebound_cat1 == `i' [aw=w1anfinwgt0], detail
  4. mat test1[`r',`c']=r(sum)
  5. mat test1[`r',`c'+1] = r(mean)*100
  6. svy: tab op_adl_`w' homebound_cat1 if homebound_cat1 == 1 | homebound_cat1 == `i'
  7. mat test1[`r',`c'+2] = e(p_Pear)
  8. local c = `c' + 3
  9. }
 10. 
. local r = `r' + 1
 11. local c = 1
 12. 
. }

. local r = 27

. local c = 1

. 
. foreach w in laun shop meal bank  meds {
  2. foreach i in 1 2 3 4{
  3. 
. sum op_iadl_`w' if homebound_cat1 == `i' [aw=w1anfinwgt0], detail
  4. mat test1[`r',`c']=r(sum)
  5. mat test1[`r',`c'+1] = r(mean)*100
  6. svy: tab op_iadl_`w' homebound_cat1 if homebound_cat1 == 1 | homebound_cat1 == `i'
  7. mat test1[`r',`c'+2] = e(p_Pear)
  8. local c = `c' + 3
  9. }
 10. 
. local r = `r' + 1
 11. local c = 1
 12. 
. }

. local c = 1

. 
. foreach w in adl iadl{
  2. foreach i in 1 2 3 4{
  3. 
. sum any_`w' if homebound_cat1 == `i' [aw=w1anfinwgt0], detail
  4. mat test1[`r',`c']=r(sum)
  5. mat test1[`r',`c'+1] = r(mean)*100
  6. svy: tab any_`w' homebound_cat1 if homebound_cat1 == 1 | homebound_cat1 == `i'
  7. mat test1[`r',`c'+2] = e(p_Pear)
  8. local c = `c' + 3
  9. }
 10. local r = `r' + 1
 11. local c = 1
 12. }

. //Evan: if you end up looking at this. I added some (working!) inefficient code for p-values.
. //Getting p-values differed based on whether or not there was weight or non-weight. I wasn't
. //sure how to account for that. So I had it so I changed the code around (like I normally
. //would have done anyway). If you know of something better let me know!
. 
. foreach weight in  "[aw=w1cgfinwgt0]" {
  2.         forvalues i=1/4 {
  3.                 mat test`i'=J(`rn',3,.) 
  4.                 foreach x in `cvars' {
  5.                         sum `x'`weight' if homebound_cat1 ==`i'
  6.                         mat test`i'[`r',`c']=r(mean)
  7.                         mat test`i'[`r',`c'+1]=r(sd)
  8.                         svy: regress `x' homebound_cat1 if homebound_cat1 == 1 | homebound_cat1 == 
> `i'
  9.                         mat test`i'[`r',`c'+2]=e(p) 
 10.                         local r=`r'+1
 11. }
 12.                 foreach x in `ivars' {
 13.                         sum `x'`weight' if homebound_cat1 ==`i'
 14.                         mat test`i'[`r',`c']=r(sum)
 15.                         mat test`i'[`r',`c'+1]=r(mean)*100
 16.                         svy: tab `x' homebound_cat1 if homebound_cat1 == 1 | homebound_cat1 == `i'
 17.                         mat test`i'[`r',`c'+2]=e(p_Pear)
 18.                         local r=`r'+1   
 19. }
 20.                 sum c1relatnshp`weight' if homebound_cat1==`i'
 21.                 mat test`i'[`r',`c']=r(N)
 22.                 mat test`i'[`r'+1,`c']=r(sum_w)
 23.                 preserve 
 24.                 keep if unique==1
 25.                 sum c1relatnshp`weight' if homebound_cat1==`i'
 26.                 mat test`i'[`r'+2,`c']=r(N)
 27.                 mat test`i'[`r'+3,`c']=r(sum_w)
 28.                 restore
 29.                 mat rownames test`i'=`cvars' `ivars' "Sample N" "Sample N Weighted" "Sample Unique 
> SP" "Sample Unique SP Weighted"
 30.                 mat colnames test`i'="Mean/N `:label homebound_cat1 `i''" "SD/%" "P"
 31.                 local r=1
 32.                 frmttable, statmat(test`i') title("Sample Characteristics by 1 year Death Weighted 
> (Full NSOC Sample)") varlabels store(tab`i') ///
>                 note("all p values diff btwn Never/Rarely and other Category")
 33. }
 34. }

. //Evan: if you end up looking at this. I added some (working!) inefficient code for p-values.
. //Getting p-values differed based on whether or not there was weight or non-weight. I wasn't
. //sure how to account for that. So I had it so I changed the code around (like I normally
. //would have done anyway). If you know of something better let me know!
. 
. foreach weight in  "[aw=w1cgfinwgt0]" {
  2.         forvalues i=1/4 {
  3.                 mat test`i'=J(`rn',3,.) 
  4.                 foreach x in `cvars' {
  5.                         sum `x'`weight' if homebound_cat1 ==`i'
  6.                         mat test`i'[`r',`c']=r(mean)
  7.                         mat test`i'[`r',`c'+1]=r(sd)
  8.                         svy: regress `x' homebound_cat1 if homebound_cat1 == 1 | homebound_cat1 == 
> `i'
  9.                         mat test`i'[`r',`c'+2]=e(p) 
 10.                         local r=`r'+1
 11. }
 12.                 foreach x in `ivars' {
 13.                         sum `x'`weight' if homebound_cat1 ==`i'
 14.                         mat test`i'[`r',`c']=r(sum)
 15.                         mat test`i'[`r',`c'+1]=r(mean)*100
 16.                         svy: tab `x' homebound_cat1 if homebound_cat1 == 1 | homebound_cat1 == `i'
 17.                         mat test`i'[`r',`c'+2]=e(p_Pear)
 18.                         local r=`r'+1   
 19. }
 20.                 sum c1relatnshp`weight' if homebound_cat1==`i'
 21.                 mat test`i'[`r',`c']=r(N)
 22.                 mat test`i'[`r'+1,`c']=r(sum_w)
 23.                 preserve 
 24.                 keep if unique==1
 25.                 sum c1relatnshp`weight' if homebound_cat1==`i'
 26.                 mat test`i'[`r'+2,`c']=r(N)
 27.                 mat test`i'[`r'+3,`c']=r(sum_w)
 28.                 restore
 29.                 mat rownames test`i'=`cvars' `ivars' "Sample N" "Sample N Weighted" "Sample Unique 
> SP" "Sample Unique SP Weighted"
 30.                 mat colnames test`i'="Mean/N `:label homebound_cat1 `i''" "SD/%" "P"
 31.                 local r=1
 32.                 frmttable, statmat(test`i') title("Sample Characteristics by 1 year Death Weighted 
> (Full NSOC Sample)") varlabels store(tab`i') ///
>                 note("all p values diff btwn Never/Rarely and other Category")
 33. }
 34. }

. //Evan: if you end up looking at this. I added some (working!) inefficient code for p-values.
. //Getting p-values differed based on whether or not there was weight or non-weight. I wasn't
. //sure how to account for that. So I had it so I changed the code around (like I normally
. //would have done anyway). If you know of something better let me know!
. 
. foreach weight in  "[aw=w1cgfinwgt0]" {
  2.         forvalues i=1/4 {
  3.                 mat test`i'=J(`rn',3,.) 
  4.                 foreach x in `cvars' {
  5.                         sum `x'`weight' if homebound_cat1 ==`i'
  6.                         mat test`i'[`r',`c']=r(mean)
  7.                         mat test`i'[`r',`c'+1]=r(sd)
  8.                         svy: regress `x' homebound_cat1 if homebound_cat1 == 1 | homebound_cat1 == 
> `i'
  9.                         mat test`i'[`r',`c'+2]=e(p) 
 10.                         local r=`r'+1
 11. }
 12.                 foreach x in `ivars' {
 13.                         sum `x'`weight' if homebound_cat1 ==`i'
 14.                         mat test`i'[`r',`c']=r(sum)
 15.                         mat test`i'[`r',`c'+1]=r(mean)*100
 16.                         svy: tab `x' homebound_cat1 if homebound_cat1 == 1 | homebound_cat1 == `i'
 17.                         mat test`i'[`r',`c'+2]=e(p_Pear)
 18.                         local r=`r'+1   
 19. }
 20.                 sum c1relatnshp`weight' if homebound_cat1==`i'
 21.                 mat test`i'[`r',`c']=r(N)
 22.                 mat test`i'[`r'+1,`c']=r(sum_w)
 23.                 preserve 
 24.                 keep if unique==1
 25.                 sum c1relatnshp`weight' if homebound_cat1==`i'
 26.                 mat test`i'[`r'+2,`c']=r(N)
 27.                 mat test`i'[`r'+3,`c']=r(sum_w)
 28.                 restore
 29.                 mat rownames test`i'=`cvars' `ivars' "Sample N" "Sample N Weighted" "Sample Unique 
> SP" "Sample Unique SP Weighted"
 30.                 mat colnames test`i'="Mean/N `:label homebound_cat1 `i''" "SD/%" "P"
 31.                 local r=1
 32.                 frmttable, statmat(test`i') title("Sample Characteristics by 1 year Death Weighted 
> (Full NSOC Sample)") varlabels store(tab`i') ///
>                 note("all p values diff btwn Never/Rarely and other Category")
 33. }
 34. }

. foreach w in eat bath toil dres insd bed  {
  2. 
. foreach i in 1 2 3 4{
  3. 
. sum op_adl_`w' if homebound_cat1 == `i' [aw=w1anfinwgt0], detail
  4. mat test1[`r',`c']=r(sum)
  5. mat test1[`r',`c'+1] = r(mean)*100
  6. svy: tab op_adl_`w' homebound_cat1 if homebound_cat1 == `i' | homebound_cat1 == 1
  7. mat test1[`r',`c'+2] = e(p_Pear)
  8. local c = `c' + 3
  9. }
 10. 
. local r = `r' + 1
 11. local c = 1
 12. 
. }

. 
. local r = 30

. local c = 1

. 
. foreach w in laun shop meal bank  meds {
  2. 
. foreach i in 1 2 3 4{
  3. 
. sum op_iadl_`w' if homebound_cat1 == `i' [aw=w1anfinwgt0], detail
  4. mat test1[`r',`c']=r(sum)
  5. mat test1[`r',`c'+1] = r(mean)*100
  6. svy: tab op_iadl_`w' homebound_cat1 if homebound_cat1 == `i' | homebound_cat1 == 1
  7. mat test1[`r',`c'+2] = e(p_Pear)
  8. local c = `c' + 3
  9. 
. }
 10. 
. local r = `r' + 1
 11. local c = 1
 12. 
. }

> 1 | homebound_cat1 == `i')

. local r = 19

. local c = 1

. foreach w in eat bath toil dres insd bed  {
  2. foreach i in 1 2 3 4{
  3. 
. sum op_adl_`w' if homebound_cat1 == `i' [aw=w1anfinwgt0], detail
  4. mat test1[`r',`c']=r(sum)
  5. mat test1[`r',`c'+1] = r(mean)*100
  6. svy: tab op_adl_`w' homebound_cat1 if homebound_cat1 == 1 | homebound_cat1 == `i'
  7. mat test1[`r',`c'+2] = e(p_Pear)
  8. local c = `c' + 3
  9. }
 10. 
. local r = `r' + 1
 11. local c = 1
 12. 
. }

. 
. local r = 27

. local c = 1

. 
. foreach w in laun shop meal bank  meds {
  2. foreach i in 1 2 3 4{
  3. 
. sum op_iadl_`w' if homebound_cat1 == `i' [aw=w1anfinwgt0], detail
  4. mat test1[`r',`c']=r(sum)
  5. mat test1[`r',`c'+1] = r(mean)*100
  6. svy: tab op_iadl_`w' homebound_cat1 if homebound_cat1 == 1 | homebound_cat1 == `i'
  7. mat test1[`r',`c'+2] = e(p_Pear)
  8. local c = `c' + 3
  9. }
 10. 
. local r = `r' + 1
 11. local c = 1
 12. 
. }

  9. }
